    <p class="text-lg text-gray-800 leading-relaxed mb-6">British Columbia’s agriculture sector is evolving rapidly, with farmers increasingly focused on sustainability, efficiency, and reducing environmental impact. In regions like Abbotsford and the Fraser Valley, growers produce a diverse range of fruits, vegetables, and specialty crops, all of which require careful handling from field to market. One of the most effective tools for sustainable operations is the reusable harvesting lug.</p>
    <p class="text-lg text-gray-800 leading-relaxed mb-10">Harvesting lugs are more than simple containers—they are critical for protecting produce, optimizing labor, reducing waste, and supporting environmentally friendly farming practices. By integrating durable, reusable lugs, farmers can improve operational efficiency while contributing to long-term sustainability goals.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Why Reusable Harvesting Lugs Matter</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">Traditional single-use containers, such as cardboard boxes or disposable plastic trays, create significant waste and recurring costs. In contrast, reusable harvesting lugs offer multiple advantages:</p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-8">
      <li><span class="font-semibold">Durability</span>: Withstand repeated use in the field, during transport, and in storage.</li>
      <li><span class="font-semibold">Protection</span>: Prevent bruising and damage to delicate crops during harvest and handling.</li>
      <li><span class="font-semibold">Efficiency</span>: Ergonomically designed for stacking, carrying, and filling.</li>
      <li><span class="font-semibold">Sustainability</span>: Reduce landfill waste and lower plastic consumption by replacing single-use alternatives.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-10">For BC farmers who care about both their bottom line and the environment, reusable harvesting lugs are a simple yet powerful solution.</p>

