    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Design Considerations for Reusable Harvesting Lugs</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">Selecting the right lug is essential to maximize benefits. BC farmers should consider:</p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-10">
      <li><span class="font-semibold">Weight Capacity</span>: Ensure lugs are appropriate for the volume and type of produce being harvested. Heavy crops require sturdier designs, while lighter crops benefit from smaller, more manageable lugs.</li>
      <li><span class="font-semibold">Stackability</span>: Lugs that stack securely reduce space requirements in storage and transport, while preventing damage to crops below.</li>
      <li><span class="font-semibold">Color-Coding</span>: Using different colors for different crops or harvest stages simplifies sorting and increases efficiency.</li>
      <li><span class="font-semibold">Ventilation</span>: Proper airflow is critical for perishable crops such as berries and leafy greens. Vented lugs prevent moisture buildup and extend shelf life.</li>
      <li><span class="font-semibold">Ergonomics</span>: Handles and lightweight designs reduce strain on workers, particularly during long harvest days.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Color Coding for Farm Efficiency</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-8">Color-coded lugs offer more than aesthetic appeal—they streamline operations:</p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-10">
      <li><span class="font-semibold">Red Lugs</span>: Strawberries or other red fruits</li>
      <li><span class="font-semibold">Green Lugs</span>: Vegetables or leafy greens</li>
      <li><span class="font-semibold">Blue Lugs</span>: Specialty crops like mushrooms or berries</li>
      <li><span class="font-semibold">Purple/Pink Lugs</span>: Small specialty items requiring delicate handling</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-10">By visually separating produce during harvest and storage, farmers can reduce sorting errors, improve organization, and save valuable time.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Sustainability and Environmental Benefits</h2>
