    </ul>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-10">In BC, where environmental stewardship is a core value of many agricultural operations, reusable harvesting lugs represent a tangible step toward sustainable farming.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Operational Tips for Maximizing Efficiency</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">To ensure the best performance and longevity of harvesting lugs, farmers should adopt the following best practices:</p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-10">
      <li><span class="font-semibold">Proper Cleaning</span>: Regular washing prevents contamination and prolongs the life of the lug.</li>
      <li><span class="font-semibold">Correct Stacking</span>: Avoid overstacking or uneven loads that can damage crops or lugs.</li>
      <li><span class="font-semibold">Strategic Placement</span>: Organize lugs near the harvest area to reduce worker movement and time.</li>
      <li><span class="font-semibold">Rotation System</span>: Use older lugs first to maintain even wear and prevent sudden failures.</li>
      <li><span class="font-semibold">Inspect Regularly</span>: Check for cracks, wear, or damage to ensure safety and durability.</li>
    </ul>

